Note = {2025 International Conference on Extended Reality-XR-Annual, Otranto,
   ITALY, JUN 17-20, 2025},
Abstract = {Extended reality (XR) technologies offer significant opportunities to
   promote sustainable cultural tourism, supporting cultural heritage
   preservation and accessibility, authentic and differentiated visitors'
   experiences, cultural tourism sites' sustainability and revitalization.
   Growing research in this area addresses the applications and design of
   storytelling with XR technologies. This paper focuses on the potential
   of cinematic storytelling through the case study of the Anime
   experience, which aims to provide a journey for exploring the Cult of
   the Purgatory Souls and its sites in the historic center of Naples
   (Italy), leveraging a semi-immersive cinematic panoramic environment and
   interactive storytelling. It presents the initial findings of this
   ongoing project relating to the design considerations for the
   development of the concept of the Anime cinematic storytelling
   experience, responding to the challenge of promoting cultural
   appreciation of this unique heritage of the city and its valorization in
   sustainable cultural tourism through an integrated, emotionally engaging
   journey through its sites, combining historical and spiritual dimensions
   into a compelling narrative.},
