   SUSTAINABLE ECONOMIC COMPETITIVE ADVANTAGE},
Year = {2019},
Pages = {617-634},
Note = {34th International-Business-Information-Management-Association (IBIMA)
   Conference, Madrid, SPAIN, NOV 13-14, 2019},
Organization = {Int Business Informat Management Assoc},
Abstract = {In this paper, the interest is focused upon the opinion of the adult
   public of entertainment over the animation industry. It is known that
   the adult people have difficulty to find animation products, because
   these kind of goods are mostly created for the young, and, on the other
   hand, when growing up, the people, in many cases, loose their interest
   for animation. Our purpose is to study if this rule is suitable for the
   anime products. We shall prove that, even if the young people watch
   animations the most, like Disney animations and anime, the adults are
   offered the option to watch anime, because there are not many other
   animations made for them. Anime is the only kind of animation which has
   relative products for all the age levels, so we can call it ``animation
   for all ages{''}.},
