Year = {2017},
Volume = {46},
Number = {2},
Pages = {221-229},
Abstract = {The starting point for this article is Nigel Palmer's contribution to
   research on Meister Eckhart. It focuses on Dominican adaptations in the
   manuscript MS. Laud Misc. 479 in the Bodleian Library, one of two
   manuscripts of the collection ``Paradisus anime intelligentis{''}
   (before 1340) which unites at least 31 sermons by Meister Eckhart
   together with sermons by Dominican Lektors. The modifications and
   abbreviations alter the text in line with Dominican doctrine. The Table
   of Contents presents a treasure trove to be used both for assessing the
   content as for questions of editorial practice. This is demonstrated by
   analysing the newly edited (Lectura Eckhardi IV) sermon 87 of the
   critical Eckhart edition.},
