   Google, Singapore, SINGAPORE, OCT 08-12, 2018},
Organization = {Assoc Comp Machinery; ACM SIGCHI; ACM SIGMOBILE; NOKIA Bell Labs; Intel;
   Microsoft; NAVER Labs; HUAWEI; Singapore Tourism Board; Singapore Pass
   Made Possible},
Abstract = {An anime music video (AMV) is a fan-made music video consisting of
   scenes from Japanese anime set to an audio track, often songs or
   promotional trailer audio. Quote MAD is one genre of AMV that consists
   of video clips of quotes. Quote MAD creators will be required to search
   and extract the necessary scenes from anime. Since both searching and
   extracting processes take a lot of time, it is a burden for the
   creators. We developed a system called PoChotto that enables the
   creators to search for the scenes that they are looking for. This system
   helps the creators to search for scenes using quote information in anime
   and provides an interface for extracting scenes. From our preliminary
   experiments, we found that the time required for searching scenes can be
   as three times faster than the conventional method. This implies the
   burden on the creator can be reduced by our system.},
