   Russian Acad Arts; Turkish Acad Sci; SGEM},
Abstract = {Even at the dawn of human civilization, there was a cult of death, which
   depending on the worldview of a people, called and represented death
   differently. With the appearance of religion this phenomenon was
   interpreted with theological positions. Dispute about the nature of
   death and its meaning as philosophers and thinkers. The phenomenon of
   ``death{''} was depicted in the literature, arts, theater, cinema. The
   death is depicted in recently appeared japan cultural phenomenon of
   anime. In this paper we consider the phenomenon of ``death{''} its
   image, sense and development in anime culture. Death is an inherent part
   of many anime plots. Depending on the nature of the character, it can be
   interpreted in different ways: as a main theme, as inevitable as fear,
