   Representations from Portugal},
Journal = {PRISMA SOCIAL},
Year = {2011},
Number = {7},
Month = {DEC},
Abstract = {My article is based in a deeper and original investigation about some
   elements of the Japanese society present in Portugal. My interest was to
   show, at the same time how Portuguese society embraces and integrates
   external influences very different from what is known, and how gender
   construction can be so distinct and so similar to what is usual in
   Portugal. I used semi-structured interviews, samples according to the
   four groups of analyze gathered from all over the country. Japan offers
   wider opportunities for gender/sex mixing and, as expected, gender
   traditional perspectives were reinforced by boys, while girls accepted
   better gender bending situations.},
