Note = {3rd International Conference on Image Processing and Media Computing
   (ICIPMC), Hefei, PEOPLES R CHINA, MAY 17-19, 2024},
Organization = {IEEE; Anhui Univ; NW Polytechn Univ; NW Univ; Shaanxi Comp Soc; Shaanxi
   Soc Image \& Graph; Univ Politecnica Cartagena},
Abstract = {In today's digital world, the sharing of images containing personal
   facial information has become a prevalent behavior. But it is essential
   to recognize that facial information, being a prominent individual
   characteristic, has found applications in various security domains.
   Consequently, the inadvertent exposure of facial information can
   potentially result in significant losses for users. Existing facial
   privacy solutions aim to modify facial features to avoid recognition by
   facial recognition systems. However, in some special application
   scenarios, authorized users (such as family members) hope to restore the
   original facial information. Therefore, To achieve face privacy
   protection and the ability to recover original facial information, this
   paper proposes a face privacy protection method based on the reversible
   animation mask network. We start by generating the high-resolution anime
   mask from the real face using an Anime Converter. Then, the real face is
   embedded within the anime mask as secret information and generates the
   anime face, which closely resembles the appearance of the anime mask.
   Authorized users can then extract the original face information from the
   anime face, and obtain the restored face which looks remarkably similar
   to the original face. Experiments show that this method has good
   visibility and can effectively protect the user's real face privacy. In
   addition, this method can almost perfectly recover real face information
   from the anime face.},
